t><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unyvinyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyvinyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 3:45:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2038.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Shadowzerker template (change of mind, kinda)</span><hr size=1> I originally had the idea to make a ~50% spec in crit/laxe/axe, full spec envenom, and ~70% spec stealth, but after hearing so much about shadowzerkers (and seeing one kick way too much ass in group already) I've decided to change, but I still want to backstab, which having 3 poisons active salvages.<br><br>So here's what I've got right now -<br><br>LAxe 10<br>Axe 9<br>Stealth 9<br>Venom 10<br>Crit 10<br><br>If I keep going at this rate (16 now) I'll not have a lot of power anywhere specifically.  I figure I can leave my crit where it is, and just use Backstab2 with a poisoned great axe as my opener, switching weapons during the hefty delay that will afford me, and then get off two more poisons right after.<br><br>I used a character planner (thanks DAoC catacombs!) to pull up this.  No wasted points at all, either!<br><br>Level 50 -<br><br>Stealth 37<br>Envenom 40 (Up to Greater Lethal)<br>Crit 10 (Backstab2!  Wow...)<br>Axe 37<br>Left Axe 37 (Double your damage, double your frost!)<br><br>I think it's pretty decent, considering the 54 points spent in crit so far only amount to 1 and a half points spent elsewhere.<br><br>So do ya think my char is salvagable as sort of a chemist/stabby zerker?<br><br>edit: forgot to take out my piccies... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unyvinyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyvinyd</A> at: 2/6/02 1:26:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uscrappinak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scrappinak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 8:42:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2038.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shadowzerker template (change of mind, kinda)</span><hr size=1> ROCKAPELLA <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 11:42:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2038.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shadowzerker template (change of mind, kinda)</span><hr size=1> Yep, that looks pretty good.  Maybe sacrifice a little venom for more LA, since you're going to rely on LA styles more than anything. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 3:48:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2038.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shadowzerker template (change of mind, kinda)</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't lower envenom.  With realm rewards and items, getting your envenom up there to 47+ is very important.  The buff system revamps have nerfed debuffs so you'll need a high envenom spec for 2 reasons:<br>1.  To get the higher level poisons.<br>2.  To use them at full effectiveness.<br><br>You might want to consider lowering stealth and/or axe a few points and getting left axe up to 39.  The 39 style is a follow up to Comeback, the evade based style.  39 style stuns.  My own personal preference would say lose 2 points of stealth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unyvinyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyvinyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 5:43:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2038.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shadowzerker template (change of mind, kinda)</span><hr size=1> The problem with that is that there are zero points left on this template.  In order to raise left axe to 39 I would have to drop 3 spec points somewhere. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unyvinyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyvinyd</A> at: 2/6/02 5:54:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 5:51:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2038.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shadowzerker template (change of mind, kinda)</span><hr size=1> I think the nerf to debuffs means you should put fewer points in poison as opposed to more... <br><br>Anyway, my template is <br><br>39 stealth<br>35 sword<br>26 envenom<br>22 critical strike<br>44 left axe<br><br>I thought it was useful to try to get perf at the last stealth autotrain level so I would have that and just let it get obsolete.  You are going to have a higher axe than left axe due to bonuses, so you may want to consider taking down axe to raise left axe.  Besides, you need a base 39 left axe to get your frost squall.  And the 44 style looks very good too. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A> at: 2/6/02 5:53:40 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=2038.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=2038.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2038.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=2038.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=2038.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2038.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2038.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td>